how to clean underarms yellow stains on white t shirts deodorant and perspiration stain removal yellow underarm shirt stains are likely caused by a combination of deodorant and perspiration many deodorants and antiperspirants contain aluminum salts when these salts are combined with laundry detergent especially in cooler water settings they are not easily dissolved and they remain on the fabric to remove the stains try soaking the shirts in warm water with an enzyme pre soak product or rubbing the soiled area with white vinegar wash in the hottest water safe for the fabric if the stain remains dampen and sprinkle stain with meat tenderizer let stand for about an hour and launder again to avoid new stains from forming always wash the shirts in the hottest water safe for the fabric also allow antiperspirant to dry completely before dressing Deodorant Dry cleaning Laundry Laundry detergent Dishwasher Textile manufacturing Washing machine Plastic Soap Vinegar Sodium percarbonate Tofu Aluminium Upholstery Menstrual cup Mattress Staining (biology) Enzyme Starch Diaper Sulfuric acid Water purification Kosher foods Jewish cuisine Manicure Urticaria Soy milk Sodium hypochlorite Dairy Body odor Acetic acid Dishwashing Hyperhidrosis Cheese Japanese toilet Sodium hydroxide Alum Nuclear fallout Psoriasis Water Sulfur Gilding Detergent Leather Cookware and bakeware Motor oil Hand washing Hard water Coffee Bedbug Jute Cuisine of the Philippines Hygiene Sewage treatment Citric acid Weaving Car washing techniques Black pepper Rice Hamster Air conditioning Gram staining Agar plate Ammonia Sweating White phosphorus incendiary Certified Nursing Assistant Bacon 1,4-dichlorobenzene Ham Diving suit Tattoo Soy protein Mouth ulcer Casting Ironing Edible salt Sento Sodium carbonate Foodborne illness Japanese tea ceremony Thermal power station Sock Sterilization (microbiology) Sugar First aid Drowning Clothing Solvent Cantonese cuisine Procter & Gamble Phosphorus Western blot Baptism Hypother